Class AStarSearch<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • AStarSearch<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type for identifier for a City, e.g E is of type Integer; City can be referred to as 1, 2, etc.

    public class AStarSearch<E>
extends java.lang.Object
    Uses an A* search algorithm, and a heuristic process to find the shortest trip through City objects that will cover all Paths in a List desiredTrips.
    Author:
    Zac Hamid - z5059915
    See Also:
    MapGraph, Heuristic

      • search

        public void search(Heuristic strategy,
          MapGraph<E> g,
          E start)
        Uses A* search to look for the shortest path in a MapGraph, starting at a certain city, using a Heuristic strategy, that includes all trips in desiredTrips.
        Parameters:
        strategy - The heuristic to apply to the search.
        g - The MapGraph to perform the search on.
        start - The starting City of the search.

      • printResults

        public void printResults(State<E> finalState,
                int nodesExpanded)
        Prints the required results of a successful search(Heuristic, MapGraph<E>, E) as:
        n nodes expanded.
        cost = Total G Cost of optimal path.
        Trip [city_1] to [city_2]
        Trip [city_2] to [city_3]
        etc.
        Parameters:
        finalState - The State the search(Heuristic, MapGraph<E>, E) completed on.
        nodesExpanded - The number of nodes taken off a PriorityQueue during the search(Heuristic, MapGraph<E>, E).
        See Also:
        State
